citeinfo.title: Annexation Areas for Ada County, Idaho for 2004

descript.abstract: This data set reflects taxing district changes and the resulting Tax Code Area changes for Ada County, Idaho as of January 1, 2004. It contains all changes to Tax Code Areas approved by the Idaho State Tax Commission from January 1, 2003 to December 31, 2003.
descript.purpose: These data are intended for geographic display and analysis of areas of change to Tax Code Areas for 2004. The data are intended to show changed areas that affect the decimation of levies, taxation on parcels, and calculation of taxes owed by utility companies. The data should be displayed and analyzed at scales appropriate for 1:500,000-scale data. No responsibility is assumed by the Idaho State Tax Commission or the State of Idaho in the use of these data.

procstep.procdesc: Determine if line was available in existing vector file in 1:24K or 1:100K from federal or state government (usually aliquot parts). If code area boundary did not follow an existing vector file, area was digitized from Tax Commission mylars. Current code areas are COGO'd in ARCINFO software in state plane NAD83 U.S. Survey foot. Polygons are built and cleaned then dissolved into large county database. Regions are then run on the database. County coverages merged into state plane zones in ArcView Geoprocessing Wizard. Output is shapefile. Each of the 3 state plane zones reprojected to IDTM. Merged IDTM zones to one statewide shapefile.
